/**
 * @file analysis.pxd
 * @brief Cython declaration file for the @c analysis C++ class.
 * @details Wraps the @c analysis class (which inherits @c notification) and
 *          exposes its sample/template registration, model training, and
 *          progress-reporting interface.  The Cython wrapper class @c Analysis
 *          owns the underlying C++ @c analysis pointer.
 */

/**
 * @class Analysis
 * @brief Python-level wrapper for the C++ @c analysis pipeline.
 * @details The @c Analysis class is the primary Python interface to AnalysisG.
 *          It owns the underlying @c analysis* pointer and keeps Python-side
 *          references to every registered template and model so they are not
 *          garbage-collected while C++ holds raw pointers to them.
 *
 * **Registration methods:**
 * - `AddSamples(path: str, label: str)` — Register a ROOT file or directory
 *   path together with a sample label used for bookkeeping.
 * - `AddEvent(ev: EventTemplate, label: str)` — Register an EventTemplate
 *   subclass instance and associate it with a sample label.
 * - `AddGraph(ev: GraphTemplate, label: str)` — Register a GraphTemplate
 *   subclass instance and associate it with a sample label.
 * - `AddSelection(selc: SelectionTemplate)` — Register a SelectionTemplate
 *   subclass instance that applies event-level cuts.
 * - `AddMetric(mex: MetricTemplate, mdl: ModelTemplate)` — Register a
 *   MetricTemplate paired with a model; also sets `PreTagEvents = True`.
 * - `AddModel(model: ModelTemplate, op: OptimizerConfig, run_name: str)` —
 *   Register a model for training with an optimizer configuration and a run
 *   name.
 * - `AddModelInference(model: ModelTemplate, run_name: str)` — Register a
 *   model for inference only (no optimizer).
 *
 * **Execution:**
 * - `Start()` — Launch the full analysis pipeline.  Handles meta-data
 *   fetching, progress display with `tqdm` bars, and post-processing
 *   transforms on registered selections.
 *
 * **Read-only property (derived):**
 * - `GetMetaData` (MetaLookup) — Returns a @c MetaLookup built from the
 *   cached @c Meta objects collected during `Start()`.  Prints a diagnostic
 *   message if no metadata was found.
 *
 * **Read/write properties (all map to fields of the internal `settings_t`):**
 * - `OutputPath` (str) — Directory where all results (graphs, plots, models)
 *   are written.
 * - `SumOfWeightsTreeName` (str) — Name of the ROOT tree containing
 *   sum-of-weights information.
 * - `kFolds` (int) — Total number of k-folds used for cross-validation.
 * - `kFold` (int | list[int]) — Which k-fold(s) to use for the current run.
 * - `Epochs` (int) — Number of training epochs.
 * - `NumExamples` (int) — Number of training examples per epoch.
 * - `TrainingDataset` (str) — Path to the HDF5 file used as training dataset
 *   (`.h5` is appended automatically if missing).
 * - `TrainSize` (float) — Percentage of data used for training (0–100, default 50).
 * - `Training` (bool) — Enable the training phase.
 * - `Validation` (bool) — Enable the validation phase.
 * - `Evaluation` (bool) — Enable the evaluation phase.
 * - `ContinueTraining` (bool) — Resume training from the last checkpoint.
 * - `nBins` (int) — Number of histogram bins used when auto-plotting
 *   kinematic distributions.
 * - `MaxRange` (int) — Upper range limit for kinematic histograms.
 * - `SetLogY` (int) — Use a logarithmic y-axis for auto-generated plots.
 * - `VarPt` (str) — Branch name mapped to transverse momentum.
 * - `VarEta` (str) — Branch name mapped to pseudorapidity.
 * - `VarPhi` (str) — Branch name mapped to azimuthal angle.
 * - `VarEnergy` (str) — Branch name mapped to energy.
 * - `Targets` (list[str]) — List of target variable names used for GNN
 *   training.
 * - `DebugMode` (bool) — Enable verbose debug output from C++.
 * - `Threads` (int) — Number of inter-operation threads for PyTorch.
 * - `IntraThreads` (int) — Number of intra-operation threads for PyTorch.
 * - `GraphCache` (str) — Path to the graph cache HDF5 file.
 * - `BatchSize` (int) — Mini-batch size used during training/evaluation.
 * - `FetchMeta` (bool) — If `True`, fetch dataset metadata from AMI during
 *   `Start()`.
 * - `BuildCache` (bool) — If `True`, build (or rebuild) the graph cache.
 * - `PreTagEvents` (bool) — Pre-tag events with model inference before
 *   running selections.
 * - `SaveSelectionToROOT` (bool) — Serialize selection results to a ROOT
 *   file alongside the pickle output.
 */
